<p>ðŸŒž Election Day was a long day for a lot of us. But the work of hand counting ballots in Mesa County probably won&#8217;t be done until Dec. 17. And that&#8217;s after the ballots were counted twice already, first using Dominion Voting Systems and then using ClearVote machines. It&#8217;s all part of a complicated dance intended to tamp down the election conspiracies emanating from embattled Mesa County Clerk Tina Peters. Peters was stripped of her election management duties and replaced by former Colorado Secretary of State Wayne Williams. <strong>Nancy Lofholm</strong> rode along with Williams as he made his rounds on Tuesday. &gt;&gt; <a target="_blank"  href="https://coloradosun.com/2021/11/03/mesa-county-elections-tina-peters/?pico=clean"><strong>STORY</strong></a><strong></strong></p>

