<p>ðŸŒž While we walked you through a crucial piece of water infrastructure on the Western Slope above, there are other elements of the state&#8217;s giant plumbing system in the news lately too. <strong>Michael Booth</strong> has been keeping us up to date with the battle between Boulder County and Denver Water over the planned half-billion dollar expansion of Gross Reservoir, and with fight to build two huge storage containers in Larimer and Weld counties for Western Slope water. &gt;&gt; <a target="_blank"  href="https://coloradosun.com/2021/11/02/gross-reservoir-expansion-boulder-county-deal/?pico=clean"><strong>STORY</strong></a><strong>, </strong><a target="_blank"  href="https://coloradosun.com/2021/11/04/northern-water-dam-pipeline-fort-collins-regulations/?pico=clean"><strong>STORY</strong></a></p>

